From dc5850594d81617f9f039a2b0201cb1198c520bc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 12:32:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add zero-dependency compute, automation and analysis layer

Introduce an agnostic runner infrastructure (standard library only, with
optional scipy/emcee/numpy/matplotlib upgrades) alongside the existing
config-driven orchestrator:

- utils/io_handlers.py: multi-encoding fallback readers, atomic writes,
  and non-destructive in-place mutation of nested JSON/JSONC/YAML/TOML
  values that preserves native comments, ordering and whitespace
  (format-aware value-span splicing, re-parse verified)
- utils/diagnostics.py: cluster post-mortem engine parsing Slurm
  stdout/stderr for OOM, wall-time, node-failure, segfault, NaN and
  traceback signatures plus wall-time/throughput profiling, with a
  workspace-wide CSV sweep
- sbatch_template.sh: variable-driven Slurm dispatch shell; all site
  values are @TOKEN@ placeholders or VARIFY_* env vars, fully decoupled
  from Python logic
- runner/: WorkflowRunner lifecycle where strategy and runtime are single
  string parameters; built-in strategies for bound-constrained
  Nelder-Mead, multiprocessed grid sweeps, affine-invariant ensemble
  MCMC, diagnostic MCMC with split-chain R-hat/ESS auto-stopping, and
  hardware scaling benchmarks; runtime=slurm renders the template and
  resubmits the calling script into the allocation
- Innovation layer wired into every run: atomic checkpoint/resume with
  SIGTERM/SIGUSR1 wall-time trapping, comprehensive pre-flight
  environment validator, and an immutable provenance record (git hash,
  seed, env map digest, timestamps) embedded in every telemetry payload
- examples/: five standalone blueprint workflows exporting telemetry and
  visualization matrices to timestamped results/ directories

Verified: all five examples end-to-end, SIGTERM interrupt/resume with
zero recomputation, comment preservation across all three formats,
seeded bit-identical reruns, mock sbatch self-dispatch; flake8 clean.

